This paper is about face recognition, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper proposes a universal representation learning framework that can deal with larger variation unseen in the given training data without leveraging target domain knowledge, which involves training a deep neural network. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories as well. Additionally, the paper involves synthesizing training data, which could fall under multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper also discusses regularization and adversarial loss, which are techniques used in cryptography (cs.CR) and could be relevant to this paper.
